org.sbolstandard.core2

Class EDAMOntology

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbolstandard.core2.EDAMOntology

  • public class EDAMOntology
extends Object
    This class provides methods for accessing EMBRACE Data and Methods (EDAM) terms and querying about their relationships.
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Zhen Zhang, Chris Myers

    • Field Detail

      • NAMESPACE

        public static final URI NAMESPACE
        Namespace of the EDAM Ontology (http://identifiers.org/edam/).

      • FORMAT

        public static final URI FORMAT
        A defined way or layout of representing and structuring data in a computer file, blob, string, message, or elsewhere. The main focus in EDAM lies on formats as means of structuring data exchanged between different tools or resources. The serialisation, compression, or encoding of concrete data formats/models is not in scope of EDAM. Format 'is format of' Data. (FORMAT).

      • SBML

        public static final URI SBML
        Systems Biology Markup Language (SBML), the standard XML format for models of biological processes such as for example metabolism, cell signaling, and gene regulation (SBML).

      • CELLML

        public static final URI CELLML
        CellML, the format for mathematical models of biological and other networks (CELLML).

      • BIOPAX

        public static final URI BIOPAX
        BioPAX is an exchange format for pathway data, with its data model defined in OWL (BIOPAX).
